Architecture plan for mtplayground/miketang84-todomvc-107

Project shape
- Use a Leptos full-stack app generated with cargo-leptos, with Axum as the server runtime.
- Keep one crate with SSR + hydration enabled rather than splitting frontend/backend crates. That keeps the shared Todo types and server functions in one place and fits the issue sequence.
- Use SQLite through SQLx with a pooled connection stored in Axum state and injected into Leptos server functions through context.

Proposed file/module structure
- Cargo.toml
  Leptos, Axum, Tokio, SQLx/sqlite, tracing, dotenvy, serde, thiserror, tower-http, http.
- src/main.rs
  Server bootstrap, env loading, tracing init, DB pool creation, Axum router, health route, Leptos routes.
- src/lib.rs
  App shell, route registration, hydration entry points, shared exports.
- src/app.rs
  Top-level Leptos app and layout.
- src/components/
  new_todo.rs, todo_item.rs, todo_list.rs, footer.rs, toggle_all.rs, mod.rs.
- src/domain/
  todo.rs for Todo model, filter enum, request/response payloads, validation helpers, mod.rs.
- src/repository/
  todos.rs for SQLx queries and persistence helpers, mod.rs.
- src/server/
  todos.rs for Leptos server functions, mod.rs.
- src/config.rs
  Environment parsing and app config.
- src/error.rs
  App error type mapped from SQLx/validation/not-found cases.
- src/state.rs
  Shared app state containing SqlitePool and config.
- style/
  todomvc.css or imported official CSS asset and any minimal overrides.
- migrations/
  SQLx migrations, starting with todos table creation.
- public/
  Static assets if cargo-leptos template uses a public dir.
- .env.example
  DATABASE_URL, RUST_LOG, LEPTOS_SITE_ADDR and any cargo-leptos runtime variables actually needed.
- Dockerfile and compose.yaml
  Multi-stage build using cargo-leptos build for production image.

Shared types
- Todo
  id: i64
  title: String
  completed: bool
  created_at: Option<OffsetDateTime/String> only if needed by schema; avoid adding fields not used by TodoMVC.
- TodoFilter enum
  All, Active, Completed with hash conversion helpers.
- Server payloads
  AddTodoInput { title }
  EditTodoInput { id, title }
  ToggleTodoInput { id, completed }
  DeleteTodoInput { id }
  Bulk action inputs for clear_completed and toggle_all.
- Result types
  Server functions return Vec<Todo>, Todo, (), or lightweight aggregate structs depending on UI needs.

Database design
- Single todos table:
  id integer primary key autoincrement
  title text not null
  completed integer not null default 0
- Keep schema minimal for TodoMVC conformance. Timestamps are optional and can be skipped unless needed later.
- Use SQLx migrations rather than ad hoc startup DDL once migrations are added. Bootstrap should still create/open the SQLite database path and run migrations on startup.

Issue dependency order
- Foundation:
  #1 cargo-leptos/Axum scaffold
  #2 SQLx + SQLite bootstrap
  #3 env vars and .env.example
  #4 tracing/logging
  #5 health route
- Data layer:
  #6 todos migration
  #7 Todo model/shared types
  #8 repository functions
- Server API:
  #9 list_todos
  #10 add_todo
  #11 toggle_todo/edit_todo
  #12 delete_todo/clear_completed/toggle_all
- UI shell:
  #13 TodoMVC CSS and base layout
  #14 new-todo input
  #15 todo list and items
  #16 inline edit
  #17 footer/filter/clear-completed
  #18 toggle-all checkbox
  #19 hash-based filter routing
- Delivery and polish:
  #20 Dockerfile + compose
  #21 README
  #22 TodoMVC conformance pass

Key design decisions
- Prefer server functions over a separate JSON REST API. The issue list already centers on Leptos server functions, and this keeps types shared and implementation smaller.
- Keep repository code free of Leptos types. Repository functions should take a SqlitePool or executor plus domain inputs and return domain models.
- Centralize validation rules in domain/server helpers:
  trim titles, reject empty titles after trim, preserve TodoMVC editing semantics.
- Use hash routing only for the filter state (`#/`, `#/active`, `#/completed`) and keep the rest of the app single-page.
- Make issue #22 a behavior pass, not a refactor. Earlier issues should keep functions/components small so final conformance work is limited to edge cases and CSS/interaction parity.

Implementation notes for later sessions
- After issue #1, verify builds with `cargo leptos build`, not plain `cargo build`.
- When SQLx is introduced, prefer runtime queries with `query_as` unless offline metadata is intentionally added later.
- Health check should stay independent of Leptos rendering and return a simple 200 response for container checks.
